---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';

const pageTitle = "About the Order";
const pageDescription = "Guardians of the Unwritten Game - Preserving the fading culture of the 19th hole";
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} pubDate={new Date()} showHeader={false}>
  <style is:global>
    /* Hide the ShareButtons (social icons at top) */
    .prose > div:first-child {
      display: none !important;
    }
    /* Hide the PostMeta (author section) */
    .prose > div:nth-child(2) {
      display: none !important;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 font-['Atkinson',sans-serif]">
    <!-- Header Section -->
    <div class="mb-14 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest !text-gray-900 dark:!text-[#34d399]">
        Guardians of the Unwritten Game
      </h1>
    </div>

    <!-- Content Section - The Manifesto -->
    <div class="space-y-10">
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest !text-gray-900 dark:!text-[#34d399] font-bold mb-3">
          I. The Origin
        </h3>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          For centuries, the official history of golf has been written in silver trophies, televised broadcasts, and immaculate scorecards. But the true game has always lived in the shadows of the clubhouse. The Order of the XIX was formed to protect what the record books ignored. We are a silent, global network of caddies, groundskeepers, archivists, and players. For 500 years, we have been the custodians of the 19th Hole cataloging the private wagers, the blood feuds, the local legends, and the unwritten rules that forged the soul of the sport.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest !text-gray-900 dark:!text-[#34d399] font-bold mb-3">
          II. The Crisis
        </h3>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          But the landscape is shifting. Today, the game is optimized, sterilized, and transactional. The fairways are full, yet the 19th hole is going quiet. Players finish their rounds, pack their trunks, and drive away. The oral tradition the stories told over heavy crystal and worn leather is dying. If we do not act, 500 years of culture will vanish.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
        <h3 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest !text-gray-900 dark:!text-[#34d399] font-bold mb-3">
          III. The Archive
        </h3>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          Necessity has forced us into the light. We have digitized our ledgers and opened the Archive. This repository contains the hearsay, the artifacts, and the lost lore of the game across 47 countries. Some stories are myth; some are absolute truth. We leave it to you to discern the difference.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest !text-gray-900 dark:!text-[#34d399] font-bold mb-3">
          IV. The Invitation
        </h3>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          The Order is governed by the Inner Circle the anonymous guardians who maintain the vaults. But we can no longer preserve this history alone. We are actively seeking the memories you carry. If your grandfather left behind a strange scorecard, if you witnessed a wager that defies belief, or if you know a legend that belongs in the permanent record... the Ledger is open to you. Welcome to the XIX.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>



